Temperature Uncertainty Viewer
Controls:
[Dropdown: Select City]    [Toggle Uncertainty]

Main Chart: Daily Temperature with Uncertainty
• Size: 800px x 400px
• X-axis: Date
• Y-axis: Temperature (°C)
• Line: Daily average temperature
• Shaded area: Min–Max temperature range
• Interaction: 
    - Hover over the chart to show a tooltip with:
        • City
        • Average temperature
        • Min-Max temperature range
• Use Case Example:
    - Identify the day with the largest temperature uncertainty for a selected city
• Toggle Button:
    - Show/Hide the uncertainty area (shaded region)

Second Chart: Bar Graph – Average Temperature per City
• Size: 700px x 350px
• X-axis: City
• Y-axis: Average temperature (°C)
• Bars: Height represents the city’s average temperature
• Interaction: 
    - Hover over bars to show tooltip with:
        • City name
        • Average temperature
• Use Case Example:
    - Compare average temperatures across all cities to find the hottest city

Visual Encoding Summary:

Line (Main Chart): Blue line = daily avg temp 
Shaded Area (Main Chart): Light blue = min–max temp range
Bars (Bar Chart): Orange bars = city average temp
Tooltip: Shows detailed numeric info 


Interactions Summary:
1. Hover on Main Chart → Tooltip + highlight data (daily temp + uncertainty)
2. Hover on Bar Chart → Tooltip (average temp per city)
3. Dropdown → Select city for Main Chart
4. Toggle Button → Show/Hide uncertainty area on Main Chart

Analysis Tasks:
Task 1: Identify High-Uncertainty Days (Main Chart)
• Select a city from the dropdown
• Find the day with the largest min-max range
• Hover to confirm exact temperatures

Task 2: Compare Average Temperatures Across Cities (Bar Chart)
• Examine the bar chart
• Identify the city with the highest average temperature
• Hover to confirm exact value


